body:
Thanks!

So now I see why this happens.
Essentially `@Context` gets translated to `@Inject` only for JAX-RS / Jakarta REST classes, for all other beans it's as if it does not even exist. 
We could debate whether this should be the case or not, but I personally think it's the right thing to do.

In your case I would just avoid the issue altogether by doing:

```java
@ApplicationScoped
public class GermanGreetingGenerator extends GreetingGenerator {

    private final HttpHeaders headers;

    public GermanGreetingGenerator(HttpHeaders headers) {
        this.headers = headers;
    }

    @Override
    public String generateGreeting() {
        return "Servus";
    }


    @Override
    public boolean handlesLanguage(String language) {
        return language.equals("de");
    }
}
```
